# Ticket 4 - Windows Workstation Connectivity

## Scenario

A user could not access internal resources or the Internet from a Windows workstation.

## Investigation

### Tools Used

* ipconfig
* Windows Network Settings
* Ping

### Commands

```cmd
ipconfig /all
ping 10.10.40.1
```

### Findings

The workstation had received an APIPA address rather than a valid network address.

```text
169.254.x.x
```

## Root Cause

The workstation was incorrectly configured and could not obtain proper network settings.

## Resolution

Configured the correct IPv4 settings including IP address, subnet mask, and default gateway.

## Skills Demonstrated

* Windows Networking
* TCP/IP Configuration
* Endpoint Troubleshooting
* Connectivity Testing

